  <h2>HTML</h2><br><br>
  <b>HTML</b>-   <em>Hyper Text Markup Language </em><br>
  HTML documents are the heart of the web.HTML made up of <br><br>
  1) Text content(what you see)<br>
  2) Markup(what it lokks like)<br>
  3) Referrence to other content(Images , vedios)<br>
  4) Links to other pages<br><br>
  <h2>HTML Tags</h2><br><br>
  <div style="background-color:#00CED1;">1) Bold Tag :- < b > content < b ></div><br>
  <div style ="background-color:Darkorchid;">2) em Tag(Italics):- < em > content < /em ></div><br>
  <div style="background-color:gold;">3) HTML Attributes :- < Tag ATTR="value"> content < /tag></div>
  <span>we use "< a >" tag to add links</span><br>
  <span><b>EX :- < a href ="www.reddit.com"> content < /a ></b></span><br><br>
  <div style="background-color:greenyellow;">4) Image Tag :-  < img > :- images </div>
  <span>EX :- < img src ="url" alt ="text"> </span><br>
  <em>Image tag doesn't have a closeing tag because it has no content .So we call it as <b>"Void Tag"</b></em><br><br>
<div style="background-color:DeepPink;">5) Line break :- < br > , < p ></div> <br>
< br > tag is a void tag(inline)<br>
< p > tag is a paragrph tag(block)<br><br>
<em><b>< br > tag use to break lines multiple times and it hasn't a closeing tag(VOID TAG),
   < p > tag also doing the same thing
   but the difference is when you useing
   < p > tag it will create a invisible box around your content it helps to design your content
 you can learn more thins about that in CSS sessions.</b></em><br><br>
 <div style="background-color:Crimson;">6) span / div </div><br>
 <em><b>difference between < span > and < div > tag is div tag create a
 invisible box around the content and both tags have closeing tags.</b></em><br><br><br>
